The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Kapil to head NCAs board

 - SUNIL GAVASKAR REMOVED FROM ONE POST AS RULING GROUP TAKES COMPLETE CHARGE 

 OF BCCI 

 Kapil Dev 

Mumbai: Former India captain Kapil Dev was Wednesday appointed chairman of the National Cricket Academys board, replacing another legend Sunil Gavaskar who, however, was retained chairman of the Board of Control for Cricket in Indias (BCCI) technical committee. 

This was on a day when another former captain Dilip Vengsarkar was appointed chairman of the selection committee. 

Former left-arm spinner Venkatapathi Raju was another new entrant in the five-member selection panel as a representative of the South Zone in place of V. B. Chandrasekhar. 

The appointments were formally announced by treasurer N. Srinivasan after the 77th annual general meeting here. 

Vengsarkar replaced Kiran More not only as the West Zone nominee, but also as the panels chief. 

The other three members of the committee Norths Bhupinder Singh, Easts Ranjib Biswal and Centrals Sanjay Jagdale were re-appointed for a two-year term. 

Sanjeev Sharma, former India pacer who has also represented Delhi and Railways, was nominated as the chairman of the national junior selection committee in place of Pravin Amre. 

Sharad Pawar was re-elected president of the Board. There was no change in the list of other office-bearers, too. 

The five elected vice-presidents were: Lalit Modi (North), Dayanand Narvekar (South), Rajeev Shukla (East), Chirayu Amin (West) and Shashank Manohar (Central). 

The BCCI, in a significant move to improve its administration, has appointed Mumbais Prof. Ratnakar Shetty as its administrative head for a five-year term. 

Shetty was the BCCIs executive secretary-in-charge till now. 

 (AGENCIES) 




